  "issue_number": 56,
  "issue_title": "bug: crystallize silently swallows approval failures and exits 0 on complete failure",
  "issue_body": "**Description**\n\n`crystallize()` in `src/vouch/sessions.py` wraps every `approve()` call in a bare `except Exception` that catches all failures and appends them to a `failures` list. When every proposal in a session fails to approve, the function returns `{\"approved\": [], \"failures\": [...]}` and the CLI prints the JSON and exits with code 0 \u2014 giving no indication that the operation completely failed.\n\nA human running `vouch crystallize <session_id>` expecting their proposals to become durable artifacts gets a silent no-op with a success exit code. The failures are only visible if they inspect the JSON output carefully.\n\n**Steps to Reproduce**\n\n1. Start a session and file one or more proposals\n2. Trigger a condition where `approve()` raises \u2014 e.g. a storage error or a status conflict\n3. Run `vouch crystallize <session_id>`\n4. Observe: exits 0, prints JSON with `\"approved\": []` and failures buried in `\"failures\"` array\n\n**Actual Behavior**\n\nAll approval failures are swallowed silently. The CLI exits 0 regardless of whether any proposals were actually approved. The user has no indication that crystallize failed.\n\n**Expected Behavior**\n\nIf all proposals fail to approve, `crystallize` should exit with a non-zero code and surface a clear error. Partial failures should at minimum print a warning so the user knows some proposals were not committed.\n\n**Environment**\n\n- Python 3.11+\n- vouch pre-1.0",
  "merged_at": "2026-05-25T12:01:04.000Z",
